In this posting:
[1] Media report, 29 Sep 2016
[2] Official press release, 28 Sep 2016

******
[1] Media report, 29 Sep 2016
Date: Thu 29 Sep 2016
Source: PUBLIKA TV [summ., edited]
http://en.publika.md/agriculture-minister-food-safety-official-on-swine-fever-in-moldova_2628517.html


The [African] swine fever is being tackled by the Moldovan authorities, after 2 foci of infection have been discovered in the north of the country.

Agriculture Minister Eduard Grama has told today [29 Sep 2016] a news conference it matters to make the people aware of the disease: "We do have problems with the [African] swine fever. Several slaughterhouses have been quarantined since spring."

Food Safety Agency ANSA deputy director Vsevolod Stamati: "We notified the Government at once about the 58 outbreaks in Ukraine. In Moldova, 10 pigs were infected, 8 died and 2 were shot dead. We sent the samples to Spain, and we expect the results tomorrow.

"The disease was brought to Moldova on St Mary Day [see comment], as people bought meat in Ukraine for a celebration."

He warns the virus must not spread out into nature and infect the wild boars: "We have done a lot informationally, disinfection and annihilating the [outbreak]. We urge people to be cautious and not keep animals older than one year."

Minister Eduard Grama says a joint struggle is necessary to have the problem solved.

