******
[2] Official press release, 28 Sep 2016
Date: Wed 28 Sep 2016
Source: Press release, Ministry of Agriculture and Food Industry of Moldova [in Romanian, machine trans., edited]
http://www.maia.gov.md/ro/comunicate-de-presa/invitatie-de-presa-2


The Ministry of Agriculture and Food Industry jointly with the National Agency for Food Safety invites media representatives to the working session that will discuss the situation regarding the detection of the 1st outbreaks of African swine fever in the Republic of Moldova, and appropriate measures to prevent its spread in the country. The event will be attended by producers, processors, importers and exporters of meat, experts from Romania, specialists of the Ministry of Agriculture and Food Industry and the National Agency for Food Safety and other relevant institutions.

The meeting will take place on Thursday, 29 Sep 2016, 13:00 in the meeting room (1st floor) of the Ministry of Agriculture and Food Industry, Stefan cel Mare Boulevard 162.

Note:
According to the latest information, 2 suspected outbreaks of African swine fever virus infection have been reported from the villages Mo≈üana and Cernoleuca in the Donduseni district.

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[Moldova borders Ukraine on its north, east and south; its western big neighbor is Romania, probably the candidate to become next in line to encounter African swine fever [ASF] (see map at http://tinyurl.com/hsp5r2j).

The distance between the 2 named Moldovan villages, where the backyard holdings are suspected to be ASF-infected, is 9.5 km [about 5.9 miles]. Since the virus is suspected to have been introduced from Ukraine with infected pig meat around St. Mary's Day (15 Aug 2016, about 6 weeks ago) its early eradication/control in Moldova is a very challenging undertaking. In particular, in view of the fact that the number of swine-keeping establishments is, according to Moldova's OIE data (2014 report) not less than 18 000: a huge number of small backyard holdings. The total number of (domestic) swine in Moldova in 2014 was, reportedly, 522 566. The 2014 number of the domestic pig population in Romania was 4 014 335 (the number of establishments not available).

For Romania's preparedness for ASF control please see the presentation discussed during EU's SCOPAFF meeting of 13-14 Sep 2016 in Brussels, at http://ec.europa.eu/food/animals/docs/reg-com_ahw_20160913_pres_asf_rou.pdf.

For a map showing all ASF outbreaks as reported to the OIE since 1 Jan 2016, see http://tinyurl.com/hv2us2d (click on the SE Europe cluster, zoom in to the Ukraine-Moldova area). - Mod.AS

A HealthMap/ProMED-mail map can be accessed at: https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=4525246,121.]
